reviews.review_text: 03-17-1991 03-18-1991 needs a matrix also so all four nights are there great job kevin

"The Elf Dance" Against All Odds In The Twilight Of The Dead's Sorjourn  They Still Could Find The Magic In The Music And Deliver It To The Awaiting Throngs. An Explanation From Nordic Mythology: "The Elf Dance" "These Elves Who In England Were Called Fairies Or Fays,Were Also Enthusiastic Musicians, And Delighted Especially In A Certain Air Known As The Elf Dance, Which Was So Irresistible That No One Who Heard It Could Refrain From Dancing. If A Mortal, Overhearing The Air, Ventured To Reproduce It, They Suddenly Found Themselves Incapable Of Stopping And Was Forced To Play On And On Until He Died Of Exhaustion, Unless He Were Deft Enough To Play The Tune Backwards, Or Some One Charitably Cut The Strings Of His Violin. His Hearers,Who Were Forced To Dance As Long As The Tones Continued, Could Only Stop When They Ceased."  What Fairies In The Early Tribal LSD Excursions Did The Dead Evoke, To Be Encompassed And To Encompass The Lucky Few That Were Able To Share In The Revalry  And Grandeur Of  This  Music Reserved For The Gods.Thank You Jerry,Phil,Bobby,Ron,Billy,Augustus,Mickey,Tom,Keith & Donna,,Brent,Bruce And Vince And All The Others That Made This Fair Voyage Possible. ~ (As Far As This Particular Show And This Particular Recording A 5 For Spirit And Performance And To Mr. Tobin A Bow For Rescuing This One Away From The Later Year Board Sound And Giving It A Mix To The Ear  Ala Augustas Owsley Stanley III. Thus A 5 If We As Mortals Must Rate.
